cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.RO 

This paper deals with scheduling in all-optical data center networks, which involves topics such as network architecture, communication protocols, and optimization algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the challenges of bufferless networks, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The proposed framework involves optimization algorithms, which could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with adapting scheduling policies, which could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.RO (Robotics).
